#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:2
#: 2fee3575a8454aa893f0993318afb580
msgid "2D Lid-Driven Cavity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:4
#: a97ea76a0f5f45918720813b64369e5c
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The lid-driven cavity is the textbook benchmark for incompressible "
"Navier-Stokes solvers. The physics is simple — a square box of fluid, the"
" top wall slides at unit speed, no-slip on the other three walls, no body"
" forces — but at moderate Reynolds numbers it already exhibits a primary "
"vortex plus secondary corner eddies that any reasonable solver must "
"reproduce. The script ``examples/fluid/cavity/cavity.py`` runs the "
"steady-state problem at :math:`\\mathrm{Re} = 100` on a triangulated unit"
" square."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:15
#: 6cc11a88cac345f7bfcb29ca93e80802
msgid "Problem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:17
#: 09c37181a3c54c758cc912edb1d14b8d
msgid "The strong form of the steady incompressible Navier-Stokes equations is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:20
#: a17479330db74d4d81d858e1f8a03357
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\rho\\, (\\mathbf{u} \\cdot \\nabla)\\mathbf{u}\n"
"\\;=\\; -\\nabla p + \\mu\\, \\Delta \\mathbf{u}\n"
"\\quad \\text{in } \\Omega,\n"
"\\qquad\n"
"\\nabla \\cdot \\mathbf{u} \\;=\\; 0,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:28
#: a41cf3f27e81461a9dae2060e8e602e6
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"with :math:`\\Omega = (0, 1)^2`, :math:`\\mu = 1/\\mathrm{Re}`, "
":math:`\\rho = 1`, and boundary conditions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:31
#: c8ba1f56b5a94ed382c5fbf83f120843
#, python-brace-format
msgid "top lid (:math:`y = 1`): :math:`\\mathbf{u} = (1, 0)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:32
#: b8130e2a58b64a63993601c56d331611
#, python-brace-format
msgid "other walls: :math:`\\mathbf{u} = \\mathbf{0}` (no-slip)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:33
#: 46a700c0befb483c92f2ec0cb70cf402
msgid "one node: :math:`p = 0` (pressure pin to fix the null space)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:37
#: bfae352b49584628999c71eee970fe5c
msgid "Weak form and stabilization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:39
#: 2e694af4360d473fa585c31a5bcae19e
msgid ""
"The standard mixed weak form treats velocity and pressure together. "
"Because the script uses **equal-order** P1-P1 elements for both, the "
"discrete LBB condition is violated and the naive Galerkin formulation has"
" spurious pressure modes. The fix is **SUPG/PSPG stabilization**: add a "
"residual-based perturbation to both the momentum and the continuity "
"equations, scaled by a mesh-size-dependent parameter :math:`\\tau`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:47
#: fa2611f230554f59afe11a5480489205
msgid ""
"The implementation is a custom :class:`~tensormesh.ElementAssembler` "
"defined locally in the example. Its ``forward`` returns a 3×3 block stamp"
" per quadrature point — two velocity components plus pressure — that "
"includes the Galerkin convection / diffusion / pressure-gradient terms "
"and the SUPG/PSPG additions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:54
#: eb7a343a33684b57870f4bc7912f375e
msgid "examples/fluid/cavity/cavity.py (essence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:91
#: 5edcac57a7194cbdbba7151788ad3ffc
msgid "Picard iteration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:93
#: afc7eb1c8e9c45a5a69f511a1ee4f032
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The convection term :math:`(\\mathbf{u}\\cdot\\nabla)\\mathbf{u}` is "
"linearized by passing the previous-iterate velocity "
":math:`\\mathbf{w}^{n}` as ``w_prev`` to the assembler:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:97
#: 399c7a8e473449a386b0a4c23fe522d1
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\rho\\, (\\mathbf{w}^{n} \\cdot \\nabla)\\mathbf{u}^{n+1}\n"
"\\;=\\; -\\nabla p^{n+1} + \\mu\\, \\Delta \\mathbf{u}^{n+1}."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:102
#: 766056b897aa4fcbad9ae827ecb1aa05
msgid ""
"This converges geometrically for moderate Reynolds numbers; the script "
"iterates until ``||u_new - u_full|| / ||u_new|| < 1e-4``, typically ~10 "
"iterations at Re=100."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:123
#: f6a0b2a66ffe433ca0759646c0e5822a
msgid "A few details that matter:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:125
#: 33912a1fd59946708d69e1abaf9f113a
msgid ""
"**DOF layout.** The unknowns are interleaved per node: ``[u_0, v_0, p_0, "
"u_1, v_1, p_1, …]``. The :class:`~tensormesh.Condenser` ``u_mask`` "
"flattens the per-node-per-component Dirichlet pattern into a single 1D "
"boolean."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:130
#: fae1dc7fc7ea49febdee88aca4f7f8d5
msgid ""
"**Pressure pin.** ``u_mask[2] = True; u_val[2] = 0.0`` clamps pressure to"
" zero at node 0 — required because pressure is only determined up to an "
"additive constant in incompressible flow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:133
#: 7f11c4b0d75f4e16a106a4235c26b36e
msgid ""
"``w_prev`` is passed by name in ``point_data`` and arrives in ``forward``"
" as the matching keyword argument; see :doc:`../../user_guide/forms` for "
"the dispatch contract."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:137
#: d57ec58cf1c740038473bdd577cad59f
msgid "Lid-driven cavity speed magnitude and pressure at Re=100"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:141
#: 86fd51fb13b84c6f8b9e30209960f224
msgid ""
"Output of ``cavity.py`` at Re = 100. Left: speed magnitude "
":math:`\\|u\\|` — the moving lid drags fluid into the upper right, "
"sweeping it down the right wall and forming the primary vortex. Right: "
"pressure field, with the characteristic high-pressure spot in the upper-"
"right corner where the lid stagnates against the wall."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:150
#: c9b04b2ca8c845889da0cd3bc15dd724
msgid "Running it"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cavity.rst:157
#: ea7d0b48399f401aa07d18b3bed62f73
msgid ""
"Console output reports relative residual at each Picard step plus the "
"final convergence message. Compare the stream-function contours "
"qualitatively against the Ghia / Ghia / Shin reference (1982) for Re=100 "
"— the location of the primary vortex center should match to within a few "
"percent."
msgstr ""

